'''秘书处大楼'''（Secretariat Building）是一座[[勒·柯布西耶|勒·柯布西耶]]设计的<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/le-corbusiers-capitol-complex-a-mess-in-dire-need-of-facelift/760264/0 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2013-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026061643/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/le-corbusiers-capitol-complex-a-mess-in-dire-need-of-facelift/760264/0 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 政府大楼。

==历史==
建于1953年，所在的[[昌迪加尔政治中心建筑群|昌迪加尔政治中心建筑群]]共包括三座建筑物和三座纪念碑：秘书处大楼（Secretariat Building）、[[议会大厦_(昌迪加尔)|议会大厦]]（Palace of Assembly）、高等法院（High Court）、开掌纪念碑（Open Hand Monument）、几何山（Geometric Hill）、光影之塔（Tower of Shadows）<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/chandigarh-s-capitol-complex-is-now-a-unesco-heritage-site-all-you-need-to-know/story-B3hHy2vXiepSGyM5uXVOYJ.html |title=capitol complex is now UNESCO heritage site |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2016-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719125628/http://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/chandigarh-s-capitol-complex-is-now-a-unesco-heritage-site-all-you-need-to-know/story-B3hHy2vXiepSGyM5uXVOYJ.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/capitol-complex-as-le-corbusier-wanted-it/635844/ |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2013-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131026061415/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/capitol-complex-as-le-corbusier-wanted-it/635844/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=128775 |title=存档副本 |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2014-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108222019/http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=128775 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2016年7月17日，该建筑和勒·柯布西耶的其他建筑作品被列为[[世界遗产|世界遗产]]<ref>{{cite web|title=The Architectural Work of Le Corbusier|url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1321/|website=UNESCO World Heritage Centre|publisher=United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization|accessdate=19 July 2016|language=en|archive-date=2016-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160409231831/https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1321/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=UNESCO1>{{Cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/buddha-bihar-nalanda-mahavihara-unesco-world-heritage-site-chandigarh/1/717209.html |title=Tile: UNESCO approves all 3 Indian nominations for heritage tag, Publisher: India Today news, Published on: 18 July 2016, Accessed on: 18 July 2016 |access-date=2020-11-15 |archive-date=2016-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160719134259/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/buddha-bihar-nalanda-mahavihara-unesco-world-heritage-site-chandigarh/1/717209.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | date=15 July 2016 | agency=UNESCO World Heritage Centre | accessdate=15 July 2016 | language=en | url=https://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1524 | title=Four sites inscribed on UNESCO’s World Heritage List | work=whc.unesco.org | archive-date=2016-07-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160716131638/https://whc.unesco.org/en/news/1524 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

